      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-04-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-06-08T18:52:21Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Asuncion Valdivia Heat Illness and Fatality Prevention Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Labor to promulgate an occupational safety or health standard on prevention of exposure to excessive heat. <i>Excessive heat</i> includes outdoor or indoor exposure to heat at levels that exceed the capacities of the body to maintain normal body functions and may cause heat-related injury, illness, or fatality.</p> <p>In addition, the bill establishes requirements concerning (1) training and education to prevent and respond to heat illness, and (2) whistle-blower protections.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
